body.description: Description: This is a laptop memory to desktop memory transfer card. It is small in size, light in weight and easy to carry. Made of high quality material, very durable and practical. A great alternative to memory RAM adapters. When trying out the memory, you can transfer 204 pin of laptop memory from three generations to 240 pin of desktop memory. Features: 1. Light in weight and small in volume. Portable, durable and practical, easy to use. 2. It is a great alternative to memory RAM adapters. 3. Use and test the DDR3 Laptop SO-DIMM in the DDR3 desktop DIMM socket. 4. Connector: SO-DIMM slot for DDR3 204 pin notebook; DDR3 240 pin desktop DIMM male connector. 5. DDR3 three generation laptop memory transfer card, laptop memory transfer to desktop memory to use (204 transfer 240)! 6. When trying out the memory, you can transfer 204 pin of laptop memory from three generations to 240 pin of desktop memory. Specifications: Type: Adapter Card Color: Green Material: Plastic + Metal Size: Approx. 13.5 * 3.8 cm / 5.3 * 1.5 inch Weight: 16g Package Include: 1 x Adapter Card

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 13, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for 8GB DDR3L SODIMM
reviews.reviewText: I had to jiggle the fit the first time, but on the second go it booted and fully recognized the DIMMs I used. The modules stand off the adapter PCB meaning you'll need 60mm clearance but it's not an issue for most desktop cases, including the mini ITX build in an SG13.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Single Rank DDR3 Works with this Adapter, Dual Rank Doesn't
reviews.reviewText: Came to my surprise that the Adapter only works with Single Rank DDR3 laptop Sticks. I had several of them but I didn't saw that Dual Ranked didnt work until i tested Stick by Stick.Ensure yourself of the Laptop sticks before to try the Adapter. Fortunately it is working on the Test machine i have.

reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars First one arrived smashed, second one just didn't work.
reviews.reviewText: Ordered one to convert some laptop RAM to desktop RAM. The SODIMM slot was crushed on the left side, rendering it unusable. Probably a carrier issue. Amazon sent a replacement which just wasn't functional--not recognized by the PC at all. This is where I get off this ride.
